The adsorption kinetics and adsorption isotherms of PAN-TETA and PAN-CDs were investigated. As shown in Fig. 3
                        , both PAN-TETA and PAN-CDs possess excellent adsorption ability for Cr(VI) in aqueous solution, with high adsorption capacity and rate. The loading of CDs had almost no effect on the adsorption properties of PAN-CDs for Cr(VI). The adsorption equilibrium of PAN-CDs for Cr(VI) was attained in 30 min, and the adsorption capacity could reach to 297.6 mg/g, which compared well with other reported adsorbents (Table 1
                        ).
